===Biography===
===Biography===
â
Miranda Frost is a [[Harvard]]-educated, gold medal-winning [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] fencer (trained by [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]'s character, Verity) posing as Graves' publicist and [[fencing]] partner. She won [[Fencing at the 2000 Summer Olympics|gold]] at the [[2000 Sydney Olympics]] by default, after Graves organized the real gold medalist's death by drug overdose. She is sent by [[M (James Bond)|M]] to work alongside Bond, but does not approve of Bond's methods. When caught by [[Mr. Kil]] and his minions, Miranda helps Bond keep incognito by kissing him. They later go to Bond's room and have [[sexual intercourse|sex]]. [[Image:Bond and Frost.jpg|200px|thumb|left|Bond and Frost]] James awakens and goes after Graves. Miranda pleads for him not to go, but he insists. Later when she pulls a gun on Graves, it is revealed that she was the one who betrayed Bond in North Korea, which led to 14 months of torture for him. At this point she reveals that she is still a traitor, and turns the gun on Bond. Bond escapes with the ring that Q gave him, and Frost and Bond fall into the jungle environment part of the Ice Palace. Frost and Jinx have a climactic fight aboard the descending plane. Frost narrowly slices Jinx in the stomach, but Jinx grabs a dagger-impaled copy of ''[[The Art of War]]'' and stabs Frost in the chest, killing her.
+
Miranda Frost is a [[Harvard]]-educated, gold medal-winning [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] fencer (trained by [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]'s character, Verity) posing as Graves' publicist and [[fencing]] partner. She won [[Fencing at the 2000 Summer Olympics|gold]] at the [[2000 Sydney Olympics]] by default, after Graves organized the real gold medalist's death by drug overdose. She is sent by [[M (James Bond)|M]] to work alongside Bond, but does not approve of Bond's methods. When caught by [[Mr. Kil]] and his minions, Miranda helps Bond keep incognito by kissing him. They later go to Bond's room and have [[sexual intercourse|sex]]. James awakens and goes after Graves. Miranda pleads for him not to go, but he insists. Later when she pulls a gun on Graves, it is revealed that she was the one who betrayed Bond in North Korea, which led to 14 months of torture for him. At this point she reveals that she is still a traitor, and turns the gun on Bond. Bond escapes with the ring that Q gave him, and Frost and Bond fall into the jungle environment part of the Ice Palace. Frost and Jinx have a climactic fight aboard the descending plane. Frost narrowly slices Jinx in the stomach, but Jinx grabs a dagger-impaled copy of ''[[The Art of War]]'' and stabs Frost in the chest, killing her.

â
'''Mr. Kil''' is a fictional character from the [[James Bond]] film, ''[[Die Another Day]]'' released in 2002. He is a henchman of the main villain, [[Gustav Graves]]. In the film he was portrayed by [[New Zealand]] [[actor]] [[Lawrence Makoare]]. Kil is first introduced alongside his Personal Assistant portrayed by [[England|English]] [[actor]] [[David Decio]], when Bond arrives in [[Iceland]]: "I am Mr Kil". [[Image:MrKil.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Kil is killed by a laser.]]Bond quips back: "Well, there's a name to die for." He [[tortures]] Jinx and straps down her hands and [[bare feet]]. He is later killed by Jinx with a [[laser]] which hits him in the back of the head and comes out of the top of his mouth while fighting with Bond. After his demise, Bond and Jinx find more uses of Kil's body: they use the laser to cut his hand off and use it to gain access to Graves's personal quarters.
+
'''Mr. Kil''' is a fictional character from the [[James Bond]] film, ''[[Die Another Day]]'' released in 2002. He is a henchman of the main villain, [[Gustav Graves]]. In the film he was portrayed by [[New Zealand]] [[actor]] [[Lawrence Makoare]]. Kil is first introduced alongside his Personal Assistant portrayed by [[England|English]] [[actor]] [[David Decio]], when Bond arrives in [[Iceland]]: "I am Mr Kil". Bond quips back: "Well, there's a name to die for." He [[tortures]] Jinx and straps down her hands and [[bare feet]]. He is later killed by Jinx with a [[laser]] which hits him in the back of the head and comes out of the top of his mouth while fighting with Bond. After his demise, Bond and Jinx find more uses of Kil's body: they use the laser to cut his hand off and use it to gain access to Graves's personal quarters.
